A devastating blast at the Hilton hotel in Taba, Egypt, killed or injured over 100 people, including at least 23 Israelis.
Suspected car bombs targeted tourists in the Sinai desert, with explosions also reported in nearby tourist camps.
Israeli officials warned of potential attacks in the region, urging immediate evacuation of Israeli tourists.
Despite ongoing security concerns, the Sinai remains a popular destination for holidaymakers.
The explosions underscore the persistent threat of violence in the area, prompting calls for heightened vigilance and caution among travelers.
Israeli authorities are coordinating efforts to ensure the safety of their citizens in the wake of the tragic events.
